Osun State government on Thursday confirmed six new cases of coronavirus from 127 Cote d’Ivoire returnees that have been tested. With this development, Osun State now has 20 cases of those who tested positive to the deadly virus in Osun. The State Commissioner for Health, Dr. Rafiu Isamontu, who confirmed the six new cases to journalists on phone, said, “The new cases with the previous case of COVID-19 have turned 20.” It would be recalled that at a press conference on Wednesday, Isamotu and the Chief Press Secretary to the Governor, Mr Ismail Omipidan disclosed that except for two cases, others who tested positive to the virus in the state were from the127 returnees that were conveyed to the state in six buses from Ogun-Osun border and taken directly to an isolation centre in Ejigbo to prevent communal mixing. The returnees according to them are from Osun, Anambra, Kwara, Oyo, Ekiti, Edo and other States but whose destination was Osun. Osun State government however appealed to the Federal Government to assist the state to curtail the spread of the virus. 